-- Poland cuts key interest rate to 2.00 percent, more than expected
-- By Pawel Florkiewicz
-- Wed Oct 08, 2014 07:21AM EDT
-- None



WARSAW, Oct 8 (Reuters) - Poland's central bank cut the key interest rate <PLINTR=ECI> by 50 basis points to a new all-time low of 2.00 percent on Wednesday, deeper than expected by analysts.

The bank cut the lombard interest rate by 100 basis points to 3.0 percent, cut the re-discount rate by 50 basis points to 2.25 percent, and left the deposit rate unchanged at 1.00 percent.